oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Framed lithograph Roll of Honor for Pvt. Henry R. Hubbs
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Henry R. Hubbs, a box maker from Knoxville, enlisted June 25, 1918. This framed lithograph was likely created before went overseas, using his photograph from Camp Gordon, Georgia, surrounded by the words "World's Great War for Democracy" and "United We Stand." Hubbs served in Co. E, 130th Inf. Regt., 33rd Division. Arriving too late for combat, he served in Luxembourg until May 20, 1919.
